HEADWORD: Cloistral
<hw>Clois"tral</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of, pertaining to,
or confined in, a cloister; recluse.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>cloisteral</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Best become a <qex>cloistral</qex> exercise.</q>
<rj><qau>Daniel.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cloistress</ent>⟦br⟧
